  "texts": [
    "For simplicity, we focus on binary treatment interventions and denote by W i t the treatment applied to unit i in round t. We assume that W i t ∼ Bernoulli(p t) for some 0 ≤ p t ≤ 1, where W i t = 1 indicates that unit i receives the treatment in round t and W i t = 0 otherwise.",
    "We denote the treatment assignments across all units in round t by ⃗ W t:= (W foot_0 t,.",
    ", W N t) ⊤, and define",
    "as the collective treatment assignment up to round t.",
    "We then use w i t, ⃗ w t, and w t to denote generic realizations of W i t, ⃗ W t, and W t, respectively."
  ],
